<div>Don't go faster than&nbsp;pace early in your race unless you have a good reason.</div><div>(It's an extra crowded start or you're feeling unusually good.)</div><div>Sometimes "official" splits aren't accurate because the watch is wrong or the split marker is incorrectly located.</div><div>What is more important is knowing generally&nbsp;how you should feel at any point in a race.</div><div><br></div>